text: Hi Krish,  Placing a ';' at the end of the plot statement will display only one set of plots. This is because jupyter will automatically render any matplotlib plots.

author: @mounabalghouthi5869
text: Add a semicolon ; after `model.plot()` to prevent the graph redundancy.  Issue was refrenced here: https://github.com/facebook/prophet/issues/396#issuecomment-354461462
